<section class="fr-testimonials">
  {% if request.path contains '/products/skinshield-diapers' %}
    <script async type="text/javascript" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets/script?presentation_type=qual&product_id=3018"></script>
    <script async type="text/javascript" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets/script?presentation_type=quant&product_id=3018"></script>
    <iframe id="frontrow-testimonials" class="iframe-frontrow-testimonials" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets?presentation_type=qual&product_id=3018"></iframe>
    
  {% elsif request.path contains '/products/wipes' %}
    <script async type="text/javascript" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets/script?presentation_type=qual&product_id=3019"></script>
    <script async type="text/javascript" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets/script?presentation_type=quant&product_id=3019"></script>
    <iframe id="frontrow-testimonials" class="iframe-frontrow-testimonials" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" src="https://app.thefrontrowhealth.com/api/widgets?presentation_type=qual&product_id=3019"></iframe>
  
  {% endif %}

  <style>
    /*
      Reserve the widget's height so it can't expand-and-shift when it loads.
      This is what makes loading="lazy" safe here: with no reserved height the iframe
      renders at ~0px and the Front Row script then resizes it. Because this sits below
      the fold, a lazy load makes that expansion happen while it is ON SCREEN — the worst
      case for CLS (an eager load expands off-screen, which CLS does not count).

      Measured rendered heights (iframe width -> height):
        747px -> 1684px   (~787px viewport)
        511px -> 1755px   (~541px viewport)
        360px -> 1870px   (~390px viewport)

      Height is ~stable (11% spread) while width swings 107%, so a per-breakpoint
      min-height works here. aspect-ratio does NOT: the ratio ranges 2.25 -> 5.19,
      because the height is driven by text reflow, not geometry.

      ⚠️ CONTENT-DEPENDENT: adding/removing testimonials changes the real height. If the
      widget ever grows past these values the shift returns — re-measure and bump them.
      Values are rounded UP so the widget never has to grow (a slightly short widget just
      leaves a little blank space, which costs nothing in CLS).
    */
    iframe.iframe-frontrow-testimonials { width: 100%; min-height: 1900px; }
    @media (min-width: 480px) { iframe.iframe-frontrow-testimonials { min-height: 1780px; } }
    @media (min-width: 768px) { iframe.iframe-frontrow-testimonials { min-height: 1700px; } }
    iframe.iframe-modal-testimonials { z-index: 99999998; }
  </style>
</section>
